# IRIS Health App

Development environment for InterSystems IRIS for Health using Docker Compose.

## Start

```powershell
docker compose up -d
```

---

## Sample Data

The file `data/sample-patient-bundle.json` contains a synthetic FHIR R4 transaction bundle used for local development and fallback mode. **No real patient data is included.** All records are fully synthetic and created solely for demonstration purposes.

### Data Format

The bundle follows the FHIR R4 transaction format (`"type": "transaction"`) and includes at minimum:

| Resource Type | Count |
|---|---|
| Patient | 1 |
| Condition | ≥ 3 (active) |
| MedicationRequest | ≥ 5 (active) |
| AllergyIntolerance | ≥ 1 |
| Observation | ≥ 10 (labs + vitals) |
| Encounter | ≥ 3 |
| CarePlan | ≥ 1 (active, with goals and activities) |

### References

The synthetic patient data is modelled after the Synthea-style bundles provided in the following repositories:

- **InterSystems FHIR Sample Data**
  https://github.com/intersystems/samples-FHIR-resource-repository
  Official InterSystems sample FHIR R4 bundles used as a structural reference for resource shape and field conventions.

- **Synthea — Synthetic Patient Population Simulator**
  https://github.com/synthetichealth/synthea
  Open-source tool that generates realistic but entirely fictional patient records in FHIR R4 format.

- **FHIR R4 Specification**
  https://hl7.org/fhir/R4/
  Normative standard defining the resource types, field names, and bundle transaction format used throughout this project.
